<H1>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </H1>
<H1>Introduction</H1>
<ul>
  <li><font size="5">Most modern systems are distributed, largely because of 
  distributed nature of the users and the information that they bring together</font></li>
  <li><font size="5">The need for scalability and robustness mandate a solution 
  that was distributed across multiple machines</font></li>
  <li><font size="5">This led to the adoption of a </font><i><font size="5">
  multi-tier architecture</font></i></li>
  <li><font size="5">The multi-tier architecture separates the management of 
  data from the business logic, which in turn is separated from the user 
  interface handling</font></li>
  <li><font size="5">It becomes easier to develop business components if the 
  component model supports <i>transactions, </i>a concept from the database 
  community that has been used for years to develop robust applications</font></li>
</ul>
  
